<TITLE> Gias Al Mamun taken into remand from hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 01 (bdnews24.com) - Gulshan police have taken controversial businessman Gias Uddin Al-Mamun into remand for three days from the prison wing of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University hospital. Gulshan police officer in-charge Obaidul Haque said Mamun was taken to the police station on Saturday for questioning in a graft case. He said Japan Bangladesh Group chairman Selim Prodhan filed the case against three people including Mamun. Dhaka Metropolitan Magistrate Rashed Kabir on Thursday granted the remand in the case which alleges the three misappropriated a total of Tk 8.46 crore from Japan Bangladesh Group. The two others taken on remand are Kauser Hasan Bappi and Rajib Siraj. bdnew
